            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <p class="faq-subtitle">Common questions about AI sales tools and how this site works.</p>
            <div class="faq-list">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">What are AI sales tools?</h3>
                    <p class="faq-answer">AI sales tools are software platforms that use artificial intelligence to automate or improve parts of the B2B sales process. They span categories including <a href="/categories/cold-outreach.html">cold email outreach</a>, <a href="/categories/lead-prospecting.html">lead prospecting</a>, <a href="/categories/data-enrichment.html">data enrichment</a>, <a href="/categories/conversation-intelligence.html">conversation intelligence</a>, <a href="/categories/sales-engagement.html">sales engagement</a>, <a href="/categories/crm-pipeline.html">CRM and pipeline management</a>, and more. Most focus on a specific stage of the sales workflow rather than trying to do everything.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">How does Sales AI Guide select and rate tools?</h3>
                    <p class="faq-answer">We synthesize evidence from 8 categories of public sources &mdash; review marketplaces (G2, Capterra, TrustRadius), practitioner communities, video walkthroughs, vendor documentation, and more &mdash; into structured Decision Snapshots. Each tool is scored across 6 dimensions with both Org Fit and Individual Rep Value composites. Pricing comes from vendor pricing pages. <a href="/methodology/">See our full methodology</a>.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">What's the difference between cold outreach tools and sales engagement platforms?</h3>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Cold outreach tools (like <a href="/compare/instantly-vs-smartlead.html">Instantly and Smartlead</a>) focus specifically on sending cold emails at scale with deliverability features like email warmup and mailbox rotation. Sales engagement platforms (like <a href="/compare/outreach-vs-salesloft.html">Outreach and Salesloft</a>) are broader, covering multi-channel sequences across email, phone, LinkedIn, and more, typically with deeper CRM integrations and team analytics.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">Are these tools suitable for small teams or only enterprise?</h3>
                    <p class="faq-answer">Both. Tools like Instantly ($37/mo), Apollo.io ($49/mo), and Lavender ($29/mo) are designed for small teams, startups, and individual reps. Enterprise platforms like Outreach, Salesloft, and ZoomInfo serve larger sales organizations with custom pricing. We list pricing on every tool so you can filter by budget quickly.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3 class="faq-question">How often is pricing and rating data updated?</h3>
                    <p class="faq-answer">We verify pricing and evidence data monthly against vendor websites, review marketplaces, and community sources. Each tool listing includes a &ldquo;Verified&rdquo; date showing when the data was last checked. Pricing and features change frequently, so we recommend checking the vendor's site directly before purchasing.</p>
